284
00:16:46,008 --> 00:16:47,217
Especially, Baby Ethos.

285
00:16:49,678 --> 00:16:51,638
Well, I became Ethos' playmate

286
00:16:51,639 --> 00:16:53,307
because they always had me over.

287
00:16:54,934 --> 00:16:56,435
Nanny, can I have my water, please?

288
00:17:08,864 --> 00:17:10,074
Okay, so going back...

289
00:17:10,908 --> 00:17:12,701
Because we were always together,

290
00:17:13,285 --> 00:17:14,285
well...

291
00:17:14,436 --> 00:17:16,021
We developed feelings
for each other.

292
00:17:17,106 --> 00:17:18,357
He courted me.

293
00:17:19,164 --> 00:17:20,390
And I said, yes.

294
00:17:20,751 --> 00:17:21,863
Two years ago.

295
00:17:21,989 --> 00:17:23,616
September 13.

296
00:17:26,298 --> 00:17:28,050
September 13?

297
00:17:28,215 --> 00:17:29,215
Yes.

298
00:17:29,927 --> 00:17:30,927
Why?

299
00:17:31,720 --> 00:17:33,305
Oh, nothing.

300
00:17:34,880 --> 00:17:37,173
Same as my anniversary with Tripp.

301
00:17:38,182 --> 00:17:39,677
What a coincidence.

302
00:17:40,710 --> 00:17:41,878
What coincidence?

303
00:17:42,640 --> 00:17:43,994
Oh, it's nothing.

304
00:17:44,358 --> 00:17:46,151
Don't mind me,
I love talking to myself.

305
00:17:47,945 --> 00:17:50,322
What's with her that Drake
dropped on his knee?

306
00:17:50,698 --> 00:17:53,659
What was I missing that
Drake would leave me?

307
00:17:54,827 --> 00:17:55,994
Oh, by the way...

308
00:17:55,995 --> 00:17:57,579
Have you been to Drake's office?

309
00:17:57,913 --> 00:17:59,873
It's in the DCL Building in Ortigas.

310
00:18:00,958 --> 00:18:01,750
Nope.

311
00:18:01,751 --> 00:18:02,918
Not really.

312
00:18:03,168 --> 00:18:04,336
Okay.

313
00:18:04,970 --> 00:18:06,055
So going back...

314
00:18:06,635 --> 00:18:09,930
I think Drake and I are
really meant for one another.

315
00:18:10,884 --> 00:18:12,386
Don't you think so too, Alys?

316
00:18:12,761 --> 00:18:13,761
Huh?

317
00:18:14,395 --> 00:18:15,687
Yeah, actually

318
00:18:15,848 --> 00:18:18,600
you two would make a great couple.

319
00:18:19,268 --> 00:18:21,979
Oh, we'll surely do, Ms. Perez.

320
00:18:23,305 --> 00:18:25,039
We'll surely do.

321
00:18:26,797 --> 00:18:28,047
By the way,

322
00:18:28,072 --> 00:18:29,281
are you done with the train?

323
00:18:29,318 --> 00:18:30,027
Yes, Ma'am.

324
00:18:30,154 --> 00:18:31,154
Oh, can I see it?

325
00:18:31,179 --> 00:18:32,179
Yes, Ma'am.

326
00:18:32,990 --> 00:18:34,073
Just a moment, Alys.

327
00:18:34,074 --> 00:18:36,076
Oh my god! That's so pretty.

328
00:18:40,686 --> 00:18:42,186
Damn it, Alys!

329
00:18:42,211 --> 00:18:43,461
You already have Tripp.

330
00:18:43,625 --> 00:18:45,836
Why are you comparing yourself to her?

331
00:18:49,840 --> 00:18:51,340
Thank you so much for coming!

332
00:18:51,341 --> 00:18:53,134
We hope you liked the food!

333
00:18:53,135 --> 00:18:54,844
Post on social media
if you can, okay?

334
00:18:54,845 --> 00:18:56,430
Thank you so much!

335
00:18:57,192 --> 00:18:59,443
Alys, congrats! Congrats!

336
00:18:59,468 --> 00:19:02,638
Thank you!
Thank you for coming!

337
00:19:04,354 --> 00:19:08,734
- Aya, my loves!
- Bestie!

338
00:19:09,735 --> 00:19:10,902
I missed you!

339
00:19:10,903 --> 00:19:13,696
- Wow, your outfit looks amazing!
- Of course!

340
00:19:13,697 --> 00:19:14,864
I love it!

341
00:19:14,865 --> 00:19:16,949
Oh, hang on, Bestie!
Got something I need to do.

342
00:19:16,950 --> 00:19:18,367
It's fine, go go!

343
00:19:18,368 --> 00:19:19,744
Classmates! Oh my god!

344
00:19:19,745 --> 00:19:21,371
What do you guys do now?

345
00:19:21,997 --> 00:19:22,997
Thank you!

346
00:19:23,732 --> 00:19:24,816
Alys!

347
00:19:24,841 --> 00:19:26,592
- Mommy!
- Congratulations!

348
00:19:27,586 --> 00:19:28,504
Congratulations, dear.

349
00:19:28,505 --> 00:19:29,837
Hey, Dad!
Thank you for coming.

350
00:19:29,838 --> 00:19:30,631
Congratulations!

351
00:19:30,632 --> 00:19:31,756
- Hi, Baby Dane!
- Alys!

352
00:19:31,757 --> 00:19:33,508
- Oh! You're so cute!
- Alys!

353
00:19:33,509 --> 00:19:35,093
Go to the cupcake tower, hurry!

354
00:19:35,094 --> 00:19:35,844
Go!

355
00:19:35,845 --> 00:19:37,261
That's a bit too "mom" of you, Mommy.

356
00:19:37,262 --> 00:19:39,848
Of course, I want to capture
this moment, Baby Dear.

357
00:19:40,099 --> 00:19:41,099
Oh!

358
00:19:41,266 --> 00:19:41,683
Here.

359
00:19:41,684 --> 00:19:43,309
Hey, get your hands off my cake!

360
00:19:43,310 --> 00:19:44,019
Give it to me.

361
00:19:44,020 --> 00:19:45,520
It's mine.
I'm taking it home.

362
00:19:45,521 --> 00:19:47,438
No, it's mine.
Go make a new one!

363
00:19:47,439 --> 00:19:48,564
I said no!
This is mine!

364
00:19:48,565 --> 00:19:49,525
It's mine now.

365
00:19:49,526 --> 00:19:50,567
I said it's mine!

366
00:19:52,732 --> 00:19:54,734
My cake!

367
00:19:55,015 --> 00:19:56,015
Alys!

368
00:19:56,156 --> 00:19:57,616
Smile!

369
00:20:00,786 --> 00:20:01,786
Different pose!

370
00:20:03,769 --> 00:20:05,140
I'm sorry, Mom.
I have to answer this.

371
00:20:05,165 --> 00:20:06,708
Alright.

372
00:20:06,959 --> 00:20:08,293
I'll be right back.

373
00:20:12,005 --> 00:20:13,132
Hey, silly!

374
00:20:13,309 --> 00:20:14,436
Hi, my silly!

375
00:20:14,834 --> 00:20:15,960
How's the store opening?

376
00:20:16,329 --> 00:20:17,664
Everything went well.

377
00:20:17,695 --> 00:20:19,195
You're the only thing missing.

378
00:20:19,252 --> 00:20:21,713
I know, but we'll be together soon.

379
00:20:22,266 --> 00:20:23,475
Just a little patience.

380
00:20:23,851 --> 00:20:25,102
I love you, silly.

381
00:20:25,992 --> 00:20:27,148
I love you, too.

382
00:20:36,081 --> 00:20:36,998
Excuse me.

383
00:20:37,072 --> 00:20:37,656
Yes, Ma'am?

384
00:20:37,657 --> 00:20:38,865
Where is Tofer?

385
00:20:38,866 --> 00:20:40,075
He’s in his office, Ma'am.

386
00:20:40,492 --> 00:20:41,492
Thank you.

387
00:20:48,709 --> 00:20:49,751
Tofer?

388
00:20:50,669 --> 00:20:51,895
Hey!

389
00:20:52,087 --> 00:20:53,881
Congrats on the opening, Perez!

390
00:20:54,344 --> 00:20:55,345
Sorry I couldn't make it.

391
00:20:55,632 --> 00:20:56,925
Why am I not surprised?

392
00:20:56,999 --> 00:20:58,583
I sent flowers!

393
00:20:58,711 --> 00:20:59,462
Here.

394
00:20:59,487 --> 00:21:00,446
For you.

395
00:21:00,555 --> 00:21:01,638
Hey!

396
00:21:02,012 --> 00:21:03,661
You really shouldn't have!

397
00:21:04,183 --> 00:21:05,075
Thank you.

398
00:21:05,100 --> 00:21:06,726
I can finally try.

399
00:21:06,727 --> 00:21:08,520
"Cupcakes by Alys".

400
00:21:10,522 --> 00:21:11,250
So...

401
00:21:11,398 --> 00:21:12,566
What brings you here?

402
00:21:13,066 --> 00:21:14,985
How can I be of service, Ms. Perez?

403
00:21:15,474 --> 00:21:17,381
Well, I'm going over to Uncle Steve's.

404
00:21:17,571 --> 00:21:18,822
What for?

405
00:21:19,198 --> 00:21:20,449
Godmother duties.

406
00:21:20,659 --> 00:21:22,843
I promised I'd go see Ethos

407
00:21:22,868 --> 00:21:24,244
for some bonding time.

408
00:21:24,578 --> 00:21:25,287
So, wait.

409
00:21:25,288 --> 00:21:26,537
You came all this way

410
00:21:26,538 --> 00:21:28,165
just to tell me that?

411
00:21:28,457 --> 00:21:29,791
You're weird.

412
00:21:30,139 --> 00:21:31,139
No.

413
00:21:32,999 --> 00:21:34,291
I just

414
00:21:34,379 --> 00:21:37,090
need to know if
Drake will be there later.

415
00:21:37,466 --> 00:21:38,466
Why?

416
00:21:40,385 --> 00:21:41,595
Don't tell me...

417
00:21:42,304 --> 00:21:43,430
Don't be an idiot!

418
00:21:44,115 --> 00:21:46,074
Oh, Tripp's going to be mad.

419
00:21:46,099 --> 00:21:47,099
I’m going to call him!

420
00:21:47,309 --> 00:21:48,477
Stop it!

421
00:21:49,144 --> 00:21:50,394
I just want to know if he'll be there

422
00:21:50,395 --> 00:21:52,439
so I can avoid him.

423
00:21:52,689 --> 00:21:54,315
I really don't want
to see that face of his.

424
00:21:54,316 --> 00:21:55,817
It'd ruin my day.

425
00:21:57,069 --> 00:22:00,071
And I also know that you're
basically made of gossip.

426
00:22:00,072 --> 00:22:01,990
You knew things before Nostrodamus did.

427
00:22:02,339 --> 00:22:04,800
Of course!
It's called thinking ahead.

428
00:22:06,323 --> 00:22:07,323
So?

429
00:22:08,914 --> 00:22:11,290
Drake will be there around 9:00 PM.

430
00:22:11,291 --> 00:22:12,209
You should be safe.

431
00:22:12,209 --> 00:22:13,209
Stop worrying.

432
00:22:13,418 --> 00:22:14,211
Okay!

433
00:22:14,211 --> 00:22:15,003
Thanks, Tofer!

434
00:22:15,003 --> 00:22:15,812
Bye!

435
00:22:15,837 --> 00:22:18,340
And that's how she is when
she gets what she wants.

436
00:22:18,674 --> 00:22:20,092
What?
You want to tag along?

437
00:22:21,176 --> 00:22:22,010
Just go! I'm busy.

438
00:22:22,010 --> 00:22:23,010
Bye!

439
00:22:30,018 --> 00:22:31,687
Aunt Katrina!

440
00:22:32,062 --> 00:22:33,105
Oh, Alys!

441
00:22:33,855 --> 00:22:34,855
Hi!

442
00:22:35,279 --> 00:22:36,488
Hello, Auntie.

443
00:22:38,568 --> 00:22:39,653
Ethos!

444
00:22:40,153 --> 00:22:42,572
Is that the toy train
that I gave you?

445
00:22:43,535 --> 00:22:45,704
Here's another gift!

446
00:22:46,285 --> 00:22:47,577
Baby Ethos!

447
00:22:48,361 --> 00:22:50,822
What brings you here, Alys?
Do you need something?

448
00:22:51,081 --> 00:22:52,415
No, Auntie.

449
00:22:52,416 --> 00:22:54,167
Just here to give a gift for Ethos.

450
00:22:56,211 --> 00:22:57,629
He's so cute, Auntie.

451
00:22:57,713 --> 00:22:59,923
He looks just like Uncle Steve!

452
00:23:00,090 --> 00:23:01,882
People always say that.

453
00:23:01,883 --> 00:23:04,320
Nobody ever said
that he looks like me.

454
00:23:08,805 --> 00:23:10,056
Lady...

455
00:23:10,976 --> 00:23:13,061
Would you kindly prepare
snacks for our guest?

456
00:23:13,228 --> 00:23:15,731
Oh, no Auntie.
There's no need!

457
00:23:16,023 --> 00:23:18,150
I'm fine, you don't have to.

458
00:23:18,567 --> 00:23:21,028
It's fine. It's not everyday
we get to see you.

459
00:23:27,868 --> 00:23:30,329
Did Drake invite you
to the wedding?

460
00:23:33,206 --> 00:23:34,791
What?

461
00:23:36,335 --> 00:23:37,919
Alys,

462
00:23:39,504 --> 00:23:42,132
I know it's not my place to say this.

463
00:23:43,633 --> 00:23:45,427
But Drake waited for you.

464
00:23:46,887 --> 00:23:48,221
He waited, Alys.

465
00:23:49,598 --> 00:23:51,600
But now, he's happy with Cristine.

466
00:23:52,934 --> 00:23:55,394
So I’m asking you not to make trouble.

467
00:23:55,395 --> 00:23:56,605
Wait, what?

468
00:23:57,397 --> 00:23:58,857
Now I'm making trouble?

469
00:23:59,191 --> 00:24:01,401
You confuse him, Alys.

470
00:24:01,818 --> 00:24:02,861
You always do.

471
00:24:07,783 --> 00:24:08,783
Alys!

472
00:24:10,151 --> 00:24:11,152
Uncle Steve!

473
00:24:11,370 --> 00:24:12,371
Hi!

474
00:24:13,580 --> 00:24:14,581
What brings you here?

475
00:24:15,832 --> 00:24:17,709
Oh, I just came by to
drop off Ethos' gift.

476
00:24:18,293 --> 00:24:19,960
He's so cute, Uncle!

477
00:24:19,961 --> 00:24:21,837
He looks just like you!

478
00:24:21,838 --> 00:24:24,174
You're just as bad as Drake.
You keep spoiling Ethos.

479
00:24:24,925 --> 00:24:27,843
How can I resist when
he's just so cute?

480
00:24:27,844 --> 00:24:29,429
That's right.

481
00:24:42,692 --> 00:24:44,027
He waited, Alys.

482
00:24:45,404 --> 00:24:47,406
But now, he's happy with Cristine.

483
00:24:48,740 --> 00:24:51,201
So, I'm asking you to not make trouble.

484
00:24:54,246 --> 00:24:55,246
Alys.

485
00:24:57,499 --> 00:25:00,043
We never got a chance
to talk at Ethos' party.

486
00:25:00,502 --> 00:25:03,547
I know, Uncle.
It was really crowded.

487
00:25:04,005 --> 00:25:05,297
I'm glad you dropped by.

488
00:25:05,298 --> 00:25:07,050
Ethos is such a smart kid.

489
00:25:07,467 --> 00:25:09,511
His mom and I started him at kindergarten.

490
00:25:10,303 --> 00:25:12,889
And he's got his mother's full attention.

491
00:25:13,515 --> 00:25:16,726
Oh no, I think you have
another little genius, Uncle.

492
00:25:17,144 --> 00:25:18,270
That's true.

493
00:25:18,812 --> 00:25:21,522
He could be as smart
as his big brother.

494
00:25:21,523 --> 00:25:23,400
I just hope he'll be nicer.

495
00:25:25,083 --> 00:25:26,668
I hope so, too.

496
00:25:28,447 --> 00:25:29,614
Uhm...

497
00:25:31,950 --> 00:25:33,118
Uncle?

498
00:25:36,788 --> 00:25:38,373
How is Drake?

499
00:25:40,250 --> 00:25:41,959
I was hoping you'd ask that.

500
00:25:41,960 --> 00:25:43,085
He's doing okay.

501
00:25:43,086 --> 00:25:44,504
He's happy with Cristine.

502
00:25:45,964 --> 00:25:48,717
And it's great that
she makes Drake happy.

503
00:25:49,301 --> 00:25:50,301
Good!

504
00:25:51,845 --> 00:25:53,597
I'm glad to know that, Uncle.

505
00:25:55,807 --> 00:25:56,850
Alys,

506
00:25:57,476 --> 00:25:59,101
don't get me wrong.

507
00:25:59,102 --> 00:26:00,729
I've always wanted you for Drake.

508
00:26:02,063 --> 00:26:03,440
But Cristine,

509
00:26:04,107 --> 00:26:06,568
I'm fine with her.
As long as Drake is happy.

510
00:26:08,570 --> 00:26:10,363
And I know she'll never leave Drake.

511
00:26:13,700 --> 00:26:14,742
Uncle,

512
00:26:14,743 --> 00:26:15,951
we're over.

513
00:26:15,952 --> 00:26:17,871
If he's happy, I'm happy.

514
00:26:18,872 --> 00:26:20,123
That's great, Alys.

515
00:26:21,458 --> 00:26:23,459
Drake and Cristine

516
00:26:23,460 --> 00:26:25,462
became bestfriends

517
00:26:26,421 --> 00:26:27,589
when you two broke up.

518
00:26:30,383 --> 00:26:32,010
After we broke up?

519
00:26:33,011 --> 00:26:33,990
Yes.

520
00:26:34,471 --> 00:26:35,763
They were classmates,

521
00:26:35,764 --> 00:26:36,973
and she always came over,

522
00:26:37,349 --> 00:26:38,433
they became close.

523
00:26:39,267 --> 00:26:42,771
Cristine was the only one who
could get him out of his shell.

524
00:26:43,188 --> 00:26:45,232
That's why I liked her.

525
00:26:45,482 --> 00:26:47,275
Am I not a good influence for Drake?

526
00:26:47,600 --> 00:26:49,769
I never taught him to do anything bad.

527
00:26:50,320 --> 00:26:53,197
I wasn't doing great at academics but,

528
00:26:53,198 --> 00:26:55,909
that doesn't mean I'm a bad influence.

529
00:26:56,093 --> 00:26:57,093
Alys, you okay?

530
00:26:58,745 --> 00:26:59,871
I'm fine, Uncle.

531
00:27:02,290 --> 00:27:03,500
Uncle?

532
00:27:04,543 --> 00:27:06,086
I just wanted to ask

533
00:27:06,336 --> 00:27:07,879
when did they get together?

534
00:27:09,130 --> 00:27:10,631
Honestly, I don't know.

535
00:27:10,632 --> 00:27:12,717
I just found out that
they were getting married.

536
00:27:13,343 --> 00:27:15,928
And I was't going to complain because

537
00:27:15,929 --> 00:27:17,089
they're great for each other.

538
00:27:21,560 --> 00:27:22,685
What about you, Alys?

539
00:27:22,686 --> 00:27:24,729
How are you?
I haven't seen you in four years!

540
00:27:25,272 --> 00:27:27,023
Steve, Alys?

541
00:27:27,190 --> 00:27:28,190
Let's eat?

542
00:27:28,483 --> 00:27:29,483
Alys, let's eat?

543
00:27:30,527 --> 00:27:31,527
Sure, Uncle.

544
00:27:32,112 --> 00:27:33,488
Okay, excuse me for a bit.

545
00:27:50,505 --> 00:27:52,381
Baby Ethos?

546
00:27:52,382 --> 00:27:54,259
Ate Alys is going now.

547
00:27:55,093 --> 00:27:56,428
Bye, Bye, Ethos.

548
00:27:57,387 --> 00:27:59,139
Bye, Alys.

549
00:28:01,349 --> 00:28:02,725
Baby Ethos?

550
00:28:02,726 --> 00:28:05,227
Can you call Ate Alys, "Ate"?

551
00:28:05,228 --> 00:28:06,228
Please?

552
00:28:06,313 --> 00:28:07,772
No, I don't want to.

553
00:28:09,024 --> 00:28:10,817
Why not, Ethos?

554
00:28:11,026 --> 00:28:13,944
Alys is not nice.
You make Drake cry.

555
00:28:13,945 --> 00:28:15,447
Alys is bad.

556
00:28:15,739 --> 00:28:17,323
What the hell, Drake?

557
00:28:17,324 --> 00:28:18,741
You hurt me back then.

558
00:28:18,742 --> 00:28:20,493
How am I the villain now?

559
00:28:25,206 --> 00:28:26,625
Ethos?

560
00:28:27,167 --> 00:28:28,335
Ethos?

561
00:28:28,918 --> 00:28:30,628
Ate Alys is not bad.

562
00:28:30,629 --> 00:28:31,296
Okay?

563
00:28:31,421 --> 00:28:32,839
Ate Alys, will tell you.

564
00:28:33,423 --> 00:28:36,176
